  <para>
	  See <link linkend="seed"><citetitle>seed</citetitle></link> which sets the global seed value for all x-class noise generators, as well as other opcodes that use a random call, such as <link linkend="grain"><citetitle>grain</citetitle></link>. <link linkend="rand"><citetitle>rand</citetitle></link>, <link linkend="randh"><citetitle>randh</citetitle></link>, <link linkend="randi"><citetitle>randi</citetitle></link>, <link linkend="rnd"><citetitle>rnd(x)</citetitle></link> and <link linkend="birnd"><citetitle>birnd(x)</citetitle></link> are not affected by seed.
  </para>

  <para>See also functions which generate random numbers in the section <link linkend="MathRndfunc"><citetitle>Random Functions</citetitle></link>.
